Defines the single string constant `CONTRACT`, the canonical agent-facing description of the `ctx-scan` CLI's behavior across its `--check`, `--prune`, `--update`, `--dry-run`, and `--stop-hook` modes.

This string is duplicated logic-as-prose: it must stay in sync with the actual CLI behavior in the rest of the crate, and a `contracts` battery test asserts the generated tool-contract block in `CLAUDE.md`/`README.md` matches `--contract`'s output exactly. Editing CLI flag behavior without updating this string will fail that check. No functions here — just the constant.